title: No entry found for key panic

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
What caused this was changing this line:

use rustc_hash::{FxHashMap as HashMap, FxHashSet as HashSet};

back to

use std::collections::{HashMap,HashSet};

This is the cargo output:

---------- Check ----------
    Checking rustdb v0.3.0 (C:\Users\pc\rust\rustdb)
    Checking rustdb-axum-example v0.1.3 (C:\Users\pc\rust\axumtest)
thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', compiler\rustc_metadata\src\rmeta\decoder\cstore_impl.rs:492:9
note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace

error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic

note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug.

note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md

note: rustc 1.57.0 (f1edd0429 2021-11-29) running on x86_64-pc-windows-msvc

note: compiler flags: -C embed-bitcode=no -C debuginfo=2 -C incremental --crate-type bin

note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden

query stack during panic:
#0 [unsafety_check_result] unsafety-checking `h_get::{closure#0}`
#1 [unsafety_check_result] unsafety-checking `h_get`
end of query stack
error: could not compile `rustdb-axum-example`
Normal Termination
Output completed (1 sec consumed).
